{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_85","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated `fails-native-image-run` job failed for `org.apache.avro:avro:1.7.5`.\n\nPreserved work branch:\nhttps://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-6958-fails-native-image-run-org.apache.avro-avro-1.7.5-9bddf09b\n\nMost likely failing stage: `fixTestNativeImageRun` failed before it produced the new-version artifacts needed for follow-up repair. The concrete evidence is that `build/reports/problems/problems-report.html` was generated for `requestedTasks: fixTestNativeImageRun`, but it only contains Gradle problem-report warnings and no preserved stack trace or task failure output. There is no generated `tests/src/org.apache.avro/avro/1.7.5/`, no `stats/org.apache.avro/avro/1.7.5/`, and no run metrics were written under `forge/script_run_metrics/` or `forge/benchmark_run_metrics/`, so dynamic-access coverage is unavailable. In the local failed worktree, `metadata/org.apache.avro/avro/1.7.5/` was created but no `reachability-metadata.json` was produced, which matches the workflow’s pre-metadata failure path.\n\nPaths to inspect:\n- `build/reports/problems/problems-report.html`\n- `metadata/org.apache.avro/avro/1.7.5/`\n- `forge/script_run_metrics/`\n- `forge/benchmark_run_metrics/`\n\nNo matching Forge run logs were preserved under `forge/logs/` or copied into `human-intervention-logs/`, so the actual native-image failure output was not retained with the preserved branch.\n\nNext steps:\n1. Re-run `./gradlew fixTestNativeImageRun -PtestLibraryCoordinates=org.apache.avro:avro:1.7.4 -PnewLibraryVersion=1.7.5 --stacktrace` from the preserved branch and capture the full Gradle/native-image output.\n2. Compare any regenerated `1.7.5` artifacts against the existing `1.7.4` baseline in `tests/src/org.apache.avro/avro/1.7.4/` and `metadata/org.apache.avro/avro/1.7.4/reachability-metadata.json`.\n3. If `metadata/org.apache.avro/avro/1.7.5/reachability-metadata.json` is produced on rerun, continue with `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.avro:avro:1.7.5`; otherwise debug the failing `fixTestNativeImageRun` step before retrying automation."}}
